oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of 75MM field gun and crew in St. Hihiel (France)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: This photogtaph shows some soldiers and a 75 mm cannon in a well camouflagued position and is associated with Homer Geiger, Btry. B, 114th Field Art., 30th Div. The shelter is made of tree brances and brush. Written in ink on the front of the Still Image "75 mm gun & crew/ 1918 ST Michele France." The 30th Div. was composed of National Guard units from Tennessee and the Carolinas.
